The paper proposes a framework for image completion, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework utilizes tensor completion algorithms, which are a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of dimensionality augmentation techniques, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI. The other two sub-categories are less likely but still relevant to the paper's content.
